cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper explores the ability of humans to understand gestures produced by telepresence robots, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and robotics (cs.RO). The study also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as the verbal descriptions were part of the experiment. Additionally, the study uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV).
